<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-497-608  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 497 608.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  May 24 1990 n1215 p30(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cambridge and the pc panacea.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gibbs, Chris.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Addenbrooke's Hospital has implemented resource management, andthis has meant restructuring its management organization andinstalling supporting information systems.andP;  The 1,000-bed facilityis introducing a network of distributed 386-based microcomputerswhich will be integrated with and will eventually replace itsveteran ITL mainframe.andP;  Decentralization will enable each servicecenter to run its own specialized applications, help avoiddependence on a single supplier, and make future changes easier.andO;An ITL-based laboratory system, a DEC VAX-based finance package,and a McDonnell Douglass personnel application will all be linkedinto the system, and case mix analysis will be brought closer tothe management units.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Hospital Information SystemsUnited KingdomHospitalSystem DesignDecentralizationManagement of EDPNetworksMicrocomputersEnd UsersApplications.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>